    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 21st ultimo relative to the extension of the period
                    fixed for the completion of the labors of the Samoan land commission, in which
                    you urge the importance of the U. S. commissioner remaining at his post until
                    the completion of the commissioner’s work.</p>
                <p>The Department’s note to you of yesterday’s date fully answers your request in
                    this regard.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
